parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wiper motor can significantly reduce visibility during rainy or snowy conditions, increasing the risk of accidents and posing a major safety hazard.
symptoms: Windshield wiper motor works intermittently
stopping at any time during operation
wiper blades may not move at all
or may only work on high speed
wiper blades may work as if they are on delay
wiper motor may only work when touched or manipulated under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A spongy brake pedal can lead to a loss of braking power, increasing the stopping distance and risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal depresses to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brake pedal has a delayed response.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corroded rotors can lead to uneven brake pad wear, reduced braking performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rotors show signs of corrosion
the brake pads wear unevenly
the vehicle vibrates or pulsates when braking
the brakes make noise when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped front brake pads and rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or pulsate when braking, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or pulsates when braking
the brake pads wear unevenly
the rotors are warped or damaged
the brakes make noise when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatback rest bolts can cause the seatback to collapse, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents, especially at higher speeds.
symptoms: The seatback rest bolts come loose
the seatback collapses backwards onto the rear seat
the seatback is not securely in place.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Track Handle/Ratchet Adjustment Lever Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat track handle/ratchet adjustment lever can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, especially when adjusting the seat while driving.
symptoms: The seat track handle/ratchet adjustment lever breaks
the seat becomes difficult to adjust
the seat moves unexpectedly while driving.
